            <t:creation/>
            <t:abstract>
                <t:p>The Flagellation of Jesus, or the Scourging at the Pillar, is a scene that occasionally appears in Ethiopian manuscripts. The scene generally shows 
                    Jesus, bound to a column, and two or more guards with the instruments of torture.
                   </t:p>
            </t:abstract>
